section.section:
For an owner-occupied residential property, the notice of intent to foreclose shall be accompanied by:
A loss mitigation application:
Instructions for completing the loss mitigation application and a telephone number to call to confirm receipt of the application;
A description of the eligibility requirements for the loss mitigation programs offered by the secured party that may be applicable to the loan secured by the mortgage or deed of trust that is the subject of the foreclosure action;
An envelope addressed to the person responsible for conducting loss mitigation analysis on behalf of the secured party for the loan secured by the mortgage or deed of trust that is the subject of the foreclosure action;
If the secured party offers prefile mediation, a notice in the form that the Commissioner of Financial Regulation prescribes by regulation that states that:
If the secured party offers prefile mediation, an application to participate in prefile mediation and instructions to complete and submit the application, all in the form that the Commissioner of Financial Regulation prescribes by regulation.

text.section:
An order to docket or a complaint to foreclose a mortgage or deed of trust on residential property shall:
Include:
If applicable, the license number of:
An affidavit stating:
Be accompanied by:
The original or a certified copy of the mortgage or deed of trust;
A statement of the debt remaining due and payable supported by an affidavit of the plaintiff or the secured party or the agent or attorney of the plaintiff or secured party;
A copy of the debt instrument accompanied by an affidavit certifying ownership of the debt instrument;
If applicable, the original or a certified copy of the assignment of the mortgage for purposes of foreclosure or the deed of appointment of a substitute trustee;
If any defendant is an individual, an affidavit that is in compliance with § 521 of the Servicemembers Civil Relief Act, 50 U.S.C. App. § 501 et seq.;
If applicable, a copy of the notice of intent to foreclose;
If the secured party and mortgagor or grantor have elected to participate in prefile mediation, the report of the prefile mediation issued by the Office of Administrative Hearings;
If the secured party and the mortgagor or grantor have not elected to participate in prefile mediation, a statement that the parties have not elected to participate in prefile mediation;
In addition to any other filing fees required by law, a filing fee in the amount of $300; and

section.section:
At a foreclosure mediation:
The mortgagor or grantor shall be present;
The mortgagor or grantor may be accompanied by a housing counselor and may have legal representation;
The secured party, or a representative of the secured party, shall be present; and
Any representative of the secured party must have the authority to settle the matter or be able to readily contact a person with authority to settle the matter.
